I dont know of any specific alternatives to the Panasonics.
Ive got a QR100 and 200, but I did buy an Olympus DS-40 a while back. Not as good as the QR&#39;s but it does get evps.
A guideline I can suggest is to look for older recorders that dont have USB (earphone jack only, like the QR&#39;s). The older recorders are more likely to have codecs that are less efficient at conversion, subsequently generate artifacts, and therefore more likely to be better at evp.
Good luck Urs.
JEFF

